cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on reducing link cost in Information-Centric Network (ICN) by optimizing content placement. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper proposes a distributed content placement strategy. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a possible category as the paper may discuss security issues related to content placement in ICN. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible category as the paper may discuss collaborative messages and coordination overhead. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a less likely category as the paper does not seem to focus on theoretical aspects of information.
